commit.message:
version 0.4.1

Changes since 0.4.0:
- `update` and `update_mmap` now return self, so they can be called
  fluently.

add missing Py_INCREFs for return values

The previous commit failed CI because of this mistake, and I was
probably just making a virtualenv mistake when I tried to test it
locally.
return self from update and update_mmap

version 0.4.0

Changes since 0.3.4:
- Add blake3.update_mmap.
expose Hasher::{update_mmap, update_mmap_rayon} as blake3.update_mmap

version 0.3.4

Changes since 0.3.3:
- Add type stubs. See blake3.pyi.
- Update PyO3 to v0.20.
upgrade pyo3 to v0.20
add Python 3.12 to CI
add blake3.pyi and add mypy to CI
update pyo3 to v0.19.0

version 0.3.3

Changes since 0.3.2:
- Change `blake3.__module__` from "blake3" to "blake3.blake3". This is
  the correct canonical path, related to some Maturin implementation
  details. This is intended to help tooling that relies on canonical
  paths, but most regular callers don't need to worry about this. See
  https://github.com/mkdocstrings/mkdocstrings/issues/451 for an example
  of a tool that needs to know this.
- Update PyO3 to v0.17.
update pyo3 to v0.17

remove the parking_lot dependency

The standard Mutex has been heavily optimized since we originally added
this dependency, and I don't think there's a performance difference
anymore.

get rid of build.py

It was always a hack, and now that we're testing the canonical import
path, the fact that it omits Maturin's generated __init__.py leads to a
test failure.

set __module__ to "blake3.blake3" in the Rust implementation

This is a correction of 07c389f257db6d3fa1fa00385b49c6b0fd262d60, which
originally set `__module__` to "blake3". For all the details, see:
- https://github.com/mkdocstrings/mkdocstrings/issues/451
- https://github.com/PyO3/maturin/discussions/1365

The C implementation is unchanged, so `__module__` is still "blake3"
there.
stop using GitHub's deprecated set-output stdout command

version 0.3.2

Changes since 0.3.1:
- `from blake3 import blake3; blake3.__module__` now correctly returns
  "blake3". Fixes #38.
- Updated Maturin to version 0.14.
remove an old Maturin workaround
check error codes in `maturin sdist`

add another retry loop to upload_github_release_asset.py

While we're at it, black format the .py files in this directory.
update Maturin to 0.14

set __module__ to "blake3"

Fixes https://github.com/oconnor663/blake3-py/issues/38.
black format .py files
remove unused Windows GNU assembly files
revendor upstream BLAKE3 version 1.3.3
document the new universal binaries for macOS in c_impl/README.md

remove Python 3.6 from CI

It hit end-of-life last December, and Maturin 0.13 no longer supports it.
pin the Maturin version in tag.yml

new docker container name for Linux builds

https://github.com/PyO3/maturin#manylinux-and-auditwheel
Maturin 0.13 doesn't support/require --no-sdist
